Basic inline styling added to HTML component:

<u><i><b>0% APR, $0 monthly payments, and no credit check!</i></b></u>

Javascript ternary operator as a validation rule for zip code 

{{/^\d{5}$/.test(zipPostalCode.value) ? '' : 'Must Be ##### Format'}}

Javascript ternary operator as a validation rule for social security number

{{/^\d{9}$/.test(ssn.value) ? '' : 'Must Be ######### Format'}}

Javascript ternary operator as a validation rule for email

{{/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/.test(emailAddress.value) ? '' : 'Not A Valid Email Format'}}

Javascript ternary operator as a validation for birthday

{{(new Date().getFullYear() - new Date(dateOfBirth.value).getFullYear() > 18 || 
    (new Date().getFullYear() - new Date(dateOfBirth.value).getFullYear() === 18 && 
    new Date().getMonth() >= new Date(dateOfBirth.value).getMonth() && 
    new Date().getDate() >= new Date(dateOfBirth.value).getDate())) ? '' : 'Must Be At Least 18 Years Of Age'}}


The submit button on the form was created to run an API request query, below are the rules I applied to success and failure responses to accomplish sandbox personas: 

Denied application that parses string 'Your application has been denied. Please review your application.' 

{{ metadata.status === 201 && data.summary.outcome === "Denied" }}

Manual Approval application that parses string 'Your application has been flagged for manual approval. Please review your application." 

{{ metadata.status === 201 && data.summary.outcome === "Manual Review" }}


